-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/africa-israel-seeks-loan-to-repay-unit-s-debt-calcalist-says.html
Africa-Israel Investments Ltd. (AFIL)  is
discussing an 850 million-shekel ($251 million) loan with
insurance companies and pension funds, Calcalist reported,
without saying where it got the information.  Proceeds will be used by its  Africa Israel Properties Ltd. (AFPR) 
unit to repay a 760 million-shekel debt to Bank Hapoalim Ltd.
related to a Tel Aviv office building and to boost cash
reserves, the newspaper said.  Africa-Israel will report as required if it has something
to say, Africa Israel spokeswoman, Dalia Azar Malimovka, told
Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in Tel Aviv at 
